;B[ss]LB[rs:1][rr:2][qp:3][ss:4][rq:A][sr:B]C[Dia.3 Correct / Dead in double pae

This shape is interesting because usually double Pae is difficult for beginners.  If Black could've played on that spot he'd be alive.  White 1 is therefore a severe move.  White takes away an eye with 3, and Black throws in with 4 to start the Pae.

But!  White can take at A.  If Black finds a pae threat it doesn't so much matter, because then White will take at B.  This means Black is dead in double pae.
\lang1042\f1\fs18
